args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Chapter 18 of the main campaign.
There ain't much point in splitting into two\nteams when we got THIS many fiends!
Hey! Get your grabby paws off her or I'll—
(Maaan, why do faeries have to be\nso tiny and weak and lame-o?)
(If I had my other form back, I could be\nkicking fiend booty like everybody else.)
That light... Is it happening again?!
('Kay, so it may not be the grown-up me,\nbut it'll do. Now lemme just break out the\nscary Notte voice aaaand...)
GET YOUR HANDS OFF HER,\nYOU JERKFIEND!
Oh man, I totally nailed that...
No problem! Now stand back, sister,\n'cause Notte's large and in charge\nlike a runaway barge!
Easy there, tiger! Ya won't do nobody\nno good if ya rush in all crazy and...\nYeah, she ain't listenin'.
Take THIS! And THIS! And one'a THESE!\nAnd some'a THOSE!
Hey, no dodging! That's totally unfair!\nOh, fine then. I'll just give you...THIIIIIS!
Yesss! Got 'em right in the kisser.\n...Wait, huh?
Nnngh... Where...? Oh, right.\nI got swept off by the stupid river.
(My adult form totally could have taken\nthat stupid fiend.)
(What's the point of getting bigger\nif I still can't fight?)
Well, you're not so tough on your own,\nbuster! I can take you on my...self?
Okay, so apparently my foot's caught\nin these tree roots. Super awkward.\nTime out for a sec.
Hey! I called time out, you big cheater!\n...HAAAALP! SOMEBODY HAAALP ME!
Phew, that was a close one!\nAre you all right?
What are you doing out here all alone?\nWe faeries all know fiends prowl this area.
Geez, you must have really hit your head.\nYes, I'm a faerie—and the name's Shirley,\nby the by.
Nice to meet you, Notte. Hold tight,\nI'll have those roots cleared in a jiff.
Oh man, thanks a million. I thought I was\ngonna be tied to that tree forever.
It's hard getting used to being big at first;\nI've definitely had my share of face-plants.
I'm guessing you're an early bloomer?\nYou seem young to have hit maturity.
Honestly, I don't really know. I just sorta\nblew up all outta nowhere, so... Huh?
Um, that actually...shouldn't be possible.\nOur bodies aren't designed to return\nto that form until we've fully matured.
Dude, I'm ten times as confused as you.\nIt feels like I've been growing and\nshrinking on rotation lately.
I still don't understand; you seem far\ntoo young to have reached full maturity.
Wait, so do all faeries get horkin' huge?
Is that a serious question? ...Er, but yes.\nWe all grow larger at a certain age.

Oh. Sorry if that was super obvious—
I'm the only faerie I've ever known,
so I never had anyone to gimme the
dirty deets on everything.
Woof! Long story. Pull up a stump\nand I'll tell you all about it...
...So you've been in the outside world\nsince you were a baby? Well, it's little\nwonder you don't know about faeries.

All right, so when faeries first enter the
mature phase of their lives, they grow
in size. And once this phase ends,
they shrink back down to normal.
It was long thought that a faerie can't\ngrow large again once fully mature,\nbut that ended up not to be true.
A secret technique was found that\nmakes it possible—a technique called\nmetamorphosis.
Can you teach it to me?!\nMetamorphosis, I mean.
I'm afraid it can only be used by faeries\nwho have passed through their large\nphase and into full maturity.
Can't hurt to try though, right?\nC'mon, pleeease?
Well, I suppose there's no harm...
If there's even a CHANCE of it working,\nI wanna try. I'm sick of being useless!
I mean, I want to protect the people who\nmatter most to me, you know?
*sigh* Well, as I said, there's no harm.\nHowever, don't get your hopes up.
I admit, you seem to be something of a\nunique case—but please remember that\nI promise nothing in terms of results.
That's totally fine by me, Shirls.\nI'll do whatever it takes!
